1.1
log
@Add radiusd(8) and radiusctl(8).  They are WIP.  radiusd(8) is a RADIUS
server and radiusctl(8) is to control the server.  radiusd(8) currently
supports bsdauth and radius (upstream radius servers) as authentication
backends.

fixes from jsg blambert
ok deraadt
@
text
@#	$OpenBSD$
PROG=		radiusd
BINDIR=		/usr/sbin
MAN=		radiusd.8 radiusd.conf.5
SRCS=		radiusd.c parse.y log.c util.c imsg_subr.c
LDADD+=		-lradius -lcrypto -levent -lutil
DPADD=		${LIBRADIUS} ${LIBCRYPTO} ${LIBEVENT} ${LIBUTIL}

.include <bsd.prog.mk>
@
